---
import '../../styles/docs.css';
---
<div class="project-docs">

  <p class="docs-note">// RU version: <a class="docs-link" href="https://github.com/nikitak-dev/nikitak-dev.github.io/blob/main/src/components/docs/multimodal-rag.ru.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">multimodal-rag.ru.md</a></p>

  <section class="docs-block">
    <h3 class="docs-heading">// WHAT IT DOES</h3>
    <p>Ask a question in plain language and get a direct answer drawn from a library of mixed-media files -- text, images, PDFs, audio, video. Each answer carries clickable sources, so you can open the exact file it came from -- down to a specific video frame or PDF page.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="docs-block">
    <h3 class="docs-heading">// TRY IT</h3>
    <p>Run the live demo on this page: pick a suggested query or type your own, hit EXEC, and see the answer with its sources.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="docs-block">
    <h3 class="docs-heading">// GOOD TO KNOW</h3>
    <p>The library is a fixed demo set curated by the developer. You can search it, but you can't add your own files -- ingesting new documents into the vector database happens off-site and isn't open to visitors.</p>
  </section>

</div>
